FBIS3-14018 "drnes055__s94068" FBIS-NES-94-055-S Document Type:Daily Report 16 Mar 1994 INDIAN VIEWS Minister Says Kashmir Open to Foreign Journalists BK1603101194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 GMT 16 Mar 94 BK1603101194 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The minister of state for external affairs, Mr. R.L. Bhatia, said over 150 foreign journalists visited Jammu and Kashmir last year. In a written reply in the Rajya Sabha today, he said Pakistan has been indulging in a disinformation campaign alleging that members of international media cannot visit Jammu and Kashmir. He said the government is taking all steps to inform the international community that there is no restriction on visits of foreign journalists to the state.
